<HL>
   Business Brief -- American Stores Co.:
   Unit Agrees to Sell Buttrey
   In $184 Million Transaction
</HL>
<DATE>
08/16/90
</DATE>
<SO>
WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE A7
</SO>
<CO>
   ASC
</CO>
<IN>
FOOD RETAILERS AND WHOLESALERS, CONVENIENCE STORES (FDR)
DRUG-BASED RETAILERS AND WHOLESALERS, PHARMACIES (RTD)
</IN>
<LP>
   American Stores Co. said its Skaggs Alpha Beta unit agreed
to sell its Buttrey Food and Drug division to an investment
group led by management of Buttrey and the merchant banking
firm of Freeman Spogli &amp; Co.
   American Stores said the transaction, expected to close in
60 days, is valued at $184 million -- $180 million in cash
and $4 million in lease assumptions. American said it will
retain $36 million in debt obligations related to the
division.
</LP>
<TEXT>
   The Buttrey division, based in Great Falls, Mont.,
operates 44 food outlets and drugstores in six states, and
has annual sales of $476 million, American said.
   Freeman Spogli, based in Los Angeles, specializes in
management-led buy-outs.
   American Stores, based in Salt Lake City, operates food
stores and drugstores in 37 states.
</TEXT>
